OL,3,CWoman 'planned' murder of ex-partner
OL,4,Cwith daughter and her partner, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FMs Lumsdon told the jury: "Mr Hillier
OL,8,Ftold Miss Goodwin he didn't trust Mrs
OL,9,FShakespeare to do it herself, he would
OL,10,Fmake sure the job was done.
OL,12,F"We suggest Mr Hillier was lying in
OL,13,Fwait for Raymond Groves and when
OL,14,FRaymond Groves arrived Mr Hillier
OL,15,Fattacked him."
OL,17,FThe prosecutor said that Goodwin told
OL,18,Fpolice in interview that she was "not
OL,19,Faware of any plan to kill or harm" Mr
OL,20,FGroves, and Hillier did not answer
OL,21,Fquestions from police.
